51.3	Peter_Weir	Peter Weir	Peter Lindsay Weir, AM (born 21 August 1944) is an Australian film director. After playing a leading role in the Australian New Wave cinema with his films such as Picnic at Hanging Rock, The Last Wave and Gallipoli, Weir directed a diverse group of American and international films—many of them major box office hits—including the Academy Award nominees Witness, Dead Poets Society, Green Card, The Truman Show and Master and Commander.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/PeterWeirApr2011.jpg/220px-PeterWeirApr2011.jpg
